climbs.name: Hells Bells
climbs.fa: Harrison Teuber, Kyle Rott - Ground up 9/15

content.description: Fun climbing connecting the chunky seams with great gear. At the last obvious placement (micro cam) traverse right on good holds towards the arete. Place your last piece in a horizontal and head up the run-out, but easy arete to the summit.
content.protection: micro - bd2, nuts, slings   2 bolt anchor w/cord

content.description: This route is a more direct finish to the 5.6 Kamps-Goldstone route and climbed by accident.Follow the chimney in between Tinker and Damn Rock (same as kamps route). Instead of going further back into the chimney and meeting up easy east ridge, climb the chimney straight up to an obvious ledge. From the ledge climb an unprotected face to the top of the east ridge.
content.location: Located in the chimney between Tinker and Damn then climbs the north faceÂ

content.description: N Side of Inner Outlet. Sits between Tinker and Baldpate View. Cool corridor with a couple good routes.
